This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the generation of synthetic medical images using generative adversarial networks. The use of progressively trained GANs also suggests that it could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the specific focus on Full Field Digital Mammograms (FFDM) suggests that it could be categorized under Medical Imaging (cs.MM) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of GANs for image synthesis also suggests that it could be categorized under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
